      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>How many electrons does each of the four nitrogen atoms in purine contribute to the aromatic <i>π</i> system?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaWNWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--9744385552b594ae281566bc6efe8a1e575e9ad3/OChem_15_06_008.jpg\" alt=\"Purine has a five-membered ring fused to a six-membered ring. Each ring consists of two nitrogen atoms and two double bonds.\">",
